# Trivy IaC misconfigurations intentionally suppressed for this PoC environment.
# Each entry documents the rationale for acceptance.

# AWS-0104: Security group rule allows unrestricted egress to any IP address
# Rationale: Inter-tier egress (web→app, app→db) is already constrained via SG references.
#            Remaining internet egress is intentionally limited to TCP 443/80 only
#            (OS package updates, AWS service endpoints). Trivy flags any 0.0.0.0/0
#            CIDR in egress regardless of port restriction.
AWS-0104

# AWS-0123: IAM group does not enforce MFA
# Rationale: Developer IAM users have programmatic access only (no console login profile).
#            MFA for API access requires a separate STS token-exchange workflow
#            (aws sts get-session-token --serial-number ... --token-code ...) which is
#            deferred to the production hardening phase.
AWS-0123

# AWS-0025: DynamoDB table does not use a customer-managed KMS key
# Rationale: State lock table holds no sensitive data beyond lock metadata.
#            AWS-managed encryption is sufficient for this PoC scope.
AWS-0025

# AWS-0024: DynamoDB point-in-time recovery not enabled
# Rationale: The DynamoDB table is used solely for Terraform state locking.
#            PITR is not needed; accidental deletion is recoverable by recreating the table.
AWS-0024

# AWS-0027: EBS volume does not use a customer-managed KMS key
# Rationale: EBS volumes are encrypted at rest (encrypted = true). CMK rotation
#            is deferred until the production environment is provisioned.
AWS-0027

# AWS-0089: S3 bucket access logging disabled
# Rationale: A dedicated logging bucket is not part of this PoC scope.
#            Access logging will be enabled when the environment is promoted to staging.
AWS-0089

# AWS-0090: S3 bucket versioning not enabled
# Rationale: The app bucket (s3_app) is an object storage bucket, not a state or backup bucket.
#            Versioning is intentionally disabled to avoid unexpected storage costs in dev.
AWS-0090

# AWS-0132: S3 bucket does not encrypt data with a customer-managed KMS key
# Rationale: Buckets are encrypted with SSE-S3 (AES-256). CMK (SSE-KMS) adoption
#            is planned for the production environment where compliance is required.
AWS-0132

# AWS-0164: Subnet auto-assigns public IP addresses
# Rationale: The web subnet is intentionally public-facing in this single-AZ PoC.
#            No NAT Gateway is deployed; public IP assignment is required for internet access.
AWS-0164

# AWS-0178: VPC Flow Logs not enabled
# Rationale: Flow Logs incur CloudWatch Logs storage costs. Deferred until staging
#            where network traffic analysis is required.
AWS-0178
